summary: This is an email chain from December 2020 discussing logistical arrangements for FBI agents from New York to travel to Los Angeles in September 2019 to interview victims in the Epstein investigation. The correspondence involves FBI personnel coordinating meeting room space and recording equipment for the interviews.

keyFacts: FBI agents from New York traveled to Los Angeles in September 2019 to interview victims as part of the Epstein investigation.
The Los Angeles FBI office (Squad C-2 Violent Crimes Against Children) offered assistance with meeting room space and recording equipment for the interviews.
The email chain confirms ongoing victim interviews in multiple locations (NY and LA) related to the Epstein case well after his death in August 2019.
The correspondence shows inter-office FBI coordination between New York and Los Angeles field offices for the investigation.
